-- Japanese Bought Net 170.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2012-08-15T23:59:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-15/japanese-bought-net-170-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Aug. 10 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 170.1 billion yen ($2.2 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 23.2 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 20.2 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 126.7 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 141 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 68.1 billion yen in stocks, and bought 610.4 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 401.3
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
